title: (x) Taylor Quality Guitars vintage western font - Nasty (Extra Ornamental) {Geoff (Lauri)}
content:
Please help me identify this vintage-style, western font... (I'm interested in the font used for the word "TAYLOR")

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20120415211443im_/http:/typophile.com/files/western-t_zoom_3482.jpg)

[https://www.taylorguitars.com/taylorware/Item.aspx?itemid=1083&categoryi...](http://web.archive.org/web/20120415211443/https:/www.taylorguitars.com/taylorware/Item.aspx?itemid=1083&categoryid=1001 "https://www.taylorguitars.com/taylorware/Item.aspx?itemid=1083&categoryid=1001")

Thanks!
author: se7en

comments.content: And if you want to clean, try [Extra Ornamental](http://web.archive.org/web/20120415211443/http:/www.dafont.com/font.php?file=extra_ornamental&page=1&nb_ppp_old=10&text=TAYLOR&nb_ppp=10&classt=alpha).

W O W !!!!

Awesome! Thanks for the quick replies....

[Eduardo Recife](http://web.archive.org/web/20120415211443/http:/typophile.com/wiki/Eduardo%20Recife) makes the best grunge fonts bar none. Gorgeous texture.

Excellent job, Geoff and Lauri. Reliable as always.
